HEADWORD: Petitionary
<hw>Pe*ti"tion*a*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Supplicatory; making a petition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Pardon Rome, and any <qex>petitionary</qex> countrymen.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Containing a petition; of the nature of a petition;
<as>as, a <ex>petitionary</ex> epistle</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Petitionee</ent>⟦br⟧
